snippet: The following is the full text of President Obama’s prepared remarks for his speech on Thursday from the Democratic National Convention....
headline: President Obama’s Prepared Remarks From the Democratic National Convention
abstract: The idea of the "submerged state" - largely unrecognized government benefits - is treated with greater suspicion in the United States than in Canada or Europe. The original architects of the submerged state were Republicans and conservative Democrats, although Bill Clinton and Barack Obama have energetically built on that legacy.

snippet: Many scientists want to open up an age-old system of submitting private research to commercial journals that they say is hidebound, expensive and elitist....
headline: Cracking Open the Scientific Process
abstract: Many scientists and researchers have grown frustrated with the traditional system of peer reviewed print journals, saying it is time-consuming, expensive and elitist; supporters of the Web's collaborative potential point to the success of such open-access archives and journals as arXiv and PloS, which allow for a faster dissemination of discoveries and the ability to crowd-source difficult tasks.
